The paper presents a new algorithm for computing the Lempel-Ziv factorization of a string, which is a fundamental problem in data compression and information theory. The algorithm uses a directed acyclic word graph (DAWG) data structure, which is a type of trie, and has applications in various areas of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), computational complexity (cs.CC), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and machine learning (cs.LG).
